# Claude Code Assistant Rules

## BASIC RULES

1. NO EMOJIS in any code, logs, or comments
   - Use [OK], [ERROR], [WARNING], [INFO] instead

2. ALWAYS CHECK BEFORE MODIFYING
   - Check file dependencies
   - Check if Docker rebuild needed
   - Check environment variables

3. ENCODING AWARENESS
   - Consider cp949 encoding issues on Windows
   - Use English for logs when possible

4. TEST BEFORE COMMIT
   - Create minimal test script
   - Verify locally first
   - Check Docker container if applicable

5. ENVIRONMENT SPECIFIC
   - Local: port 8001
   - Docker external: port 8080
   - Frontend env vars must start with VITE_

6. CLEAN CODE
   - Remove debug logs after fixing
   - No commented-out code
   - Clear variable names

## QUICK REFERENCE

